Looting and burning of vehicles and buildings is a criminal offence. People who are involved in these acts must be brought to book and punished accordingly. You can’t show your anger and frustrations through violence. There are better ways to make your grievances heard instead of endangering the lives of others. I urge the leaders involved to help calm the situation. Authorities should intervene before this madness gets out of hand. We can’t allow this situation to escalate while we fold our arms and watch. Acornhoek The situation has now escalated to purely criminal activity by tsotsis who took advantage. The law should take its full course and those who are responsible for the wanton looting must be arrested and prosecuted. The economy has already suffered from the effects of Covid-19 and that should be enough. This letter wins R200. Call Cheryl at the office to collect your prize. X Deputy Editor